  "body": "### Component\n\nAnvil\n\n### Have you ensured that all of these are up to date?\n\n- [X] Foundry\n- [X] Foundryup\n\n### What version of Foundry are you on?\n\nforge 0.2.0 (f540aa9 2022-09-09T00:09:51.262286Z)\n\n### What command(s) is the bug in?\n\n_No response_\n\n### Operating System\n\nmacOS (Intel)\n\n### Describe the bug\n\nAnvil does not appear to track `totalDifficulty` when mining blocks.\r\n\r\n### Reproduction steps\r\n1. Fork ethereum mainnet using default Anvil settings:\r\n```\r\n% anvil --fork-url https://some-forkable-url\r\n```\r\n\r\n2. The last recorded block shows a `totalDifficulty`:\r\n```\r\n% cast block 15504216\r\n\r\n...\r\ntimestamp            1662747868\r\ntotalDifficulty      58344397744196789300626\r\ntransactions:        [\r\n...\r\n```\r\n\r\n3. Perform a payment using the provided accounts:\r\n```\r\n% cast send 0xf39fd6e51aad88f6f4ce6ab8827279cfffb92266 --value 1 --from 0x70997970c51812dc3a010c7d01b50e0d17dc79c8\r\n```\r\n\r\n7. The produced block does not show a `totalDifficulty`:\r\n```\r\n% cast block 15504217\r\n\r\n...\r\ntimestamp            1662747957\r\ntotalDifficulty      \r\ntransactions:        [\r\n...\r\n```",
